I"�<h1 id="good-content-design">Good content design</h1>

<h2 id="start-with-the-user">Start with the user</h2>

<p>Good web content is designed around user needs. It’s what the user needs from your service and not what you want to tell them.</p>

<p>Start by <a href="/essex-county-council-digital-manual/Service-Transformation-team/User-need">learning who you are designing for</a>.</p>

<h2 id="designing-good-content">Designing good content</h2>

<p>Content should be:</p>

<ul>
  <li>simple</li>
  <li>clear</li>
  <li>direct</li>
  <li>easy to read</li>
  <li>authoritative</li>
  <li>You need to make it as easy as possible for users to find, read the content and complete their task.</li>
</ul>

<p>Good content:</p>

<ul>
  <li>helps users complete tasks</li>
  <li>helps build trust</li>
  <li>makes users return to your content</li>
  <li>encourages use of online services</li>
  <li>Use this guide to help you design your content to meet user needs.</li>
</ul>
